main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted moving in a southwesterly direction over Oakland, California.
interesting points: The object moved at an estimated speed of 500-550 mph.
The object was described as a fiery orange color.
The object was observed at an altitude between 2,020 and 4,700 feet.
The report mentions that there were no aircraft operations in the congested area at the time of the sighting.
The report concludes that the object was possibly a weather balloon, based on information received from the senior controller at the Oakland Air Route Traffic Control.
